                <h3>University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign</h3>
                <p class="timeline-role">Mechanical Engineering Research Assistant · Combustion Diagnostics Lab</p>

                <ul>
                  <li class="typewrite">Designed and fabricated utility fixtures for off-campus combustion research using Fusion 360, 3D printing, and aluminum assemblies.</li>
                  <li class="typewrite">Created mounting components for HVAC, electrical, and laboratory instruments.</li>
                  <li class="typewrite">Gathered researcher requirements and developed budget-conscious fixture designs to improve lab usability and setup efficiency.</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="trait-list">
                  <span>Research</span>
                  <span>Fusion 360</span>
                  <span>Fabrication</span>
                  <span>3D Printing</span>
                  <span>Lab Setup</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
